17, 18. Here Horace seems to be thinking of the Commonwealth as much as of the ship. The contrast is between the two moments, a few hours ago when the ship was struggling for existence in the storm‚ and now when it is at the haven's mouth, but still not quite safe. His feeling towards it then was ‘a hopeless beart-sickening‚' now it is ‘a fond yearning and anxious care.'
